    "description": "The Fascination reads like a Sunday lifestyle magazine printed on warm cream paper: editorial photography dominates, type stays quiet, and color only appears as small chromatic punctuation. A geometric sans (Graphik) carries all functional text while a handwritten script (Qwitcher Grypen) interrupts section headers with hand-drawn personality. The vivid electric blue is reserved exclusively for links, borders, and interactive accents — never as filled button backgrounds — creating a system where the page feels mostly monochrome and blue is the only 'switched on' signal. Cards and product reviews float on subtle parchment surfaces (#efe8dc) against a cream canvas (#fbfbf7), with generous spacing and a tight 6px radius on interactive elements that keeps everything feeling tactile and paper-like.",
    "customSections": [
